headline: Kimco Realty: Fundamentals Are Strong, But Valuation Limits Upside (For Now)
summary: Kimco Realty's balance sheet remains resilient, featuring 99.8% fixed-rate debt, A- credit ratings, and well-staggered maturities. See why KIM stock is a Buy.
